data.enText: produced or happening every three months
a quarterly meeting of the board
a magazine, etc. published four times a year

tr: a periodical that is published every quarter (or four issues per year)
of or relating to or consisting of a quarter
in diagonally opposed quarters of an escutcheon
example: two coats of arms borne quarterly

value.def: A quarterly event happens four times a year, at intervals of three months.

example.ex: ...the latest Bank of Japan quarterly survey of 5,000 companies.
example.tran: 日本银行对5,000家公司的最新季度调查

example.ex: It makes no difference whether dividends are paid quarterly or annually.
example.tran: 红利按季发放还是按年发放没有什么差别。

value.tran: 三个月一次的;按季度的

value.def: A quarterly is a magazine that is published four times a year, at intervals of three months.

example.ex: The quarterly had been a forum for sound academic debate.
example.tran: 这本季刊曾经是进行颇有见地的学术讨论的论坛。

example.ex: ...'Foreign Policy', a quarterly journal published in Paris.
example.tran: 《外交政策》——一本在巴黎出版的季刊
